Usage: get_lib_clock_tree_path_delay [-help] -base_pin <term>
                                     [-delay_type {max min}] [-edge {rise fall}]
                                     [-mode <string>] [-power_domain <pd>]
                                     -transition <float> -view <analysis_view>

-help                     # Prints out the command usage
-base_pin <term>          # base pin name ((term), required)
-delay_type {max min}     # delay type(default: max) (enum, optional)
-edge {rise fall}         # signal direction(default: rise) (enum, optional)
-mode <string>            # analysis mode name (string, optional)
-power_domain <pd>        # power domain name ((pd), optional)
-transition <float>       # input transition time
                          # (float, required, min=0, max=99)
-view <analysis_view>     # analysis view name ((analysis_view), required)